# promptgym/<type>/ = a Claude-Code-native AIOS, scoped BY CWD (NO CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR — mirrors the
# CEO). The agent auto-injects <type>/CLAUDE.md (project memory, via the cwd->root walk) +
# <type>/.claude/{skills,rules,agents} (native project-level discovery), and keeps its OWN per-dir
# doc-mirror under <type>/docs/ + <type>/context/.
#
# VERSIONED (the AIOS source):
#   <type>/CLAUDE.md
#   <type>/.claude/{rules,agents,skills}/  AUTHORED content — force-added (`git add -f`): the
#       monorepo ROOT .gitignore excludes every `.claude/`, so authored .claude content is
#       committed with -f; the runtime symlinks below are NOT force-added, so they never commit.
#   <type>/docs/{mirror,vision}, <type>/context/journal  (the per-dir doc-mirror layer)
#
# Doc-mirror skills + the universal-worker subagent are SYMLINKED into <type>/.claude/{skills,
# agents}/ at agent init (env-specific runtime, regenerated per environment) — already excluded by
# the root `.claude/` rule, so they never commit.

# the shared convo registry for the gym agents (alias -> claude session_id)
/.promptgym/
# defensive: stray claude config/session cruft. The cwd-only model writes session state to the
# USER config (~/.claude), NOT here — but keep these so any legacy scoped-runtime leftovers (from
# the old CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=<dir> model) stay ignored.
/*/.claude.json
/*/.credentials.json
/*/.last-cleanup
/*/mcp-needs-auth-cache.json
/*/projects/
/*/sessions/
/*/backups/
/*/session-env/
/*/shell-snapshots/
/*/telemetry/
/*/statsig/
/*/todos/
